# Kubernetes Lecture 11 – Volumes

---

# 1. Default Volumes in Kubernetes

Every container gets its own writable filesystem (provided by the container runtime such as containerd or CRI-O).

Kubernetes also provides its own volumes that can be mounted into Pods.

The most common default volume is the **Projected Volume**.

---

# 2. Projected Volume

A Projected Volume combines data from multiple Kubernetes sources into a single directory inside the container.

It can contain:

- ServiceAccount Token
- ConfigMap
- Secret
- Downward API

```
Projected Volume
        │
 ┌──────┼─────────┐
 │      │         │
Token ConfigMap DownwardAPI
```

---

