# 8. EmptyDir Volume

EmptyDir is a temporary volume created when the Pod starts.

Characteristics

- Created when Pod starts
- Shared among all containers in the Pod
- Deleted when Pod is deleted

```
Pod
 ├── Container A
 ├── Container B
 └── EmptyDir
```

---

# EmptyDir YAML

```yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: emptydir-demo

spec:
  containers:
  - name: app
    image: nginx

    volumeMounts:
    - name: cache
      mountPath: /cache

  volumes:
  - name: cache
    emptyDir:
      sizeLimit: 500Mi
```

Create Pod

```bash
kubectl apply -f emptydir.yaml
```

Verify

```bash
kubectl get pod emptydir-demo -o yaml
```

Enter Pod

```bash
kubectl exec -it emptydir-demo -- /bin/bash
```

Go to mounted directory

```bash
cd /cache
```

Create file

```bash
echo "Hello Kubernetes" > file.txt
```

Location on Worker Node

```
/var/lib/kubelet/pods/<UID>/volumes/kubernetes.io~empty-dir/
```

Delete Pod

```bash
kubectl delete pod emptydir-demo
```

Result

```
Pod Deleted
      ↓
EmptyDir Deleted
```

---

# EmptyDir Storage

Default

```
Disk
```

RAM

```yaml
volumes:
- name: cache
  emptyDir:
    medium: Memory
    sizeLimit: 500Mi
```

Useful for

- Cache
- Temporary Files
- Session Data

---

# Practical Example

```
Application
      ↓
Generates Logs
      ↓
Stored in EmptyDir
      ↓
Backup Script
      ↓
Permanent Storage
```

If Pod is deleted before backup, logs are lost.

